Serbia Mulls Emergency Loan for Galenika, B92 Broadcaster Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-06-21T05:47:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/serbia-mulls-emergency-loan-for-galenika-b92-broadcaster-says.html
Galenika ,  Serbia ’s state-run
drugmaker, may receive government help to pay its short-term
debt of 12 million euros ($17 million) and avoid a halt in
production,  B92 broadcaster  reported, citing Health Minister
Zoran Stankovic.  Galenika’s debts have reached 90 million euros while
wholesalers owe it some 110 million euros for delivered drugs,
the broadcaster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  